{
  "doc_id": "27365",
  "text": "Obviously, there are numerous Pareto-optimal solutions that satisfy the above condition. It is possible to generate all Paretooptimal points by iteratively decreasing the value of C NoTrade k . Abounacer et al. proposed a solution approach using the epsilon constraint method that iteratively generates all Paretooptimal solutions [CITATION_1] . However, it is computationally expensive because the solution time increases exponentially according to the number of households. Zhang et al. proposed a lexicographic minimax method that distributes the cost savings in a proportional fair way among the households. However, it also results in a more complex optimization problem, requiring to solve the problem iteratively in polynomial time [CITATION_2] .",
